The paper discusses methods for making neural network architectures more flexible and efficient, which are topics commonly studied in the sub-field of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper specifically focuses on language modeling tasks, which fall under the sub-field of natural language processing (cs.CL). The paper also discusses the use of adaptive parameterization, which is a technique commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper mentions the use of LSTM, a type of recurrent neural network commonly used in computer vision tasks (cs.CV).
